<div class="campaign">
	<h3>IdeaBook</h3>
	<p>We created a way to crowd-source which product enhancement ideas were the best ones to add to the system by asking our users to submit ideas and then vote on their favorite. The most popular ideas rose to the top and were added; less popular ideas were encouraged to influence others by comments and screenshots.</p>
</div>

<div class="campaign">
	<h3>Travis Blog</h3>
	<p>We launched our blog in August 2008; late to the social media scene, The <a href="http://blog.travisoft.com">blog</a> launched and built a level of trust between our users. When the 2009 Stimulus package launched, we used the blog as a vehicle to disseminate information quickly and answer user questions. Without the blog, our phone lines would have been overloaded and we could not have kept up.</p>
</div>

<div class="campaign">
	<h3>Permission Email on Blog</h3>
	<p>For customers who do not use RSS, we built a campaign to deliver information to them via email -- but only if they requested it. Over 20% of our customer base signed up for the email delivery; that percentage surprised even me!</p>
</div>

